Package org.mort11.led

Class LED

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.SendableBase
      • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
        • org.mort11.led.LED

  • public final class LED
extends edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
    This class contains a subsystem for the LEDs. Several different commands can be run on the LED subsystem. Values for the LEDs are inverted. True turns an LED off, false turns it on.
    Version:
    05/31/2018
    Author:
    Joshua Ciffer

        public void changeIntakeColor​()

      • setLEDCommand

        public void setLEDCommand​(edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Command ledCommand)
        Changes the command that the LEDs run when the robot is changed from teleop, to auton, to disabled. -Teleop mode: IntakeColorChanger() -Auton mode: ChangeAllianceColor() -Disabled mode: DisableLEDs() -End game: CycleEndGameColors() getCurrentCommand().cancel() could throw a NullPointerException if there is no current command assigned to the subsystem, so a try and catch statement is necessary. If there is no current command assigned to the subsystem, then no other action required.
        Parameters:
        ledCommand - The command to run on the LEDs.
